  cssExtra={['/css/about.css', '/css/service-pages.css']}
>
  <main>
<section class="service-hero service-hero-assembly">
            <div class="service-wrap service-hero-grid">
                <div>
                    <div class="service-kicker">PCB assembly</div>
                    <h1>Prototype PCB Assembly for Fast Design Verification</h1>
                    <p class="service-lead">XFPCB helps customers build prototype PCB assemblies with BOM review, PCB fabrication coordination, SMT/THT assembly and inspection planning.</p>
                    <div class="service-actions"><a class="service-primary" href="#quote">Request a Quote</a><a class="service-secondary" href="/support/">Ask Technical Support</a></div>
                    <div class="service-tags"><span>prototype PCB assembly</span><span>fast prototype PCBA</span><span>prototype PCBA manufacturer</span><span>DFM review</span><span>prototype to production</span></div>
                </div>
                <figure class="service-visual"><img src="/images/smt-pcba-assembly-process.png" alt="Prototype PCB Assembly at XFPCB" loading="eager"><figcaption>Prototype PCB Assembly production support from XFPCB includes file review, manufacturing preparation, inspection and export communication for global electronics customers.</figcaption></figure>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="service-section"><div class="service-wrap service-grid"><div><h2>XFPCB Prototype PCB Assembly Service</h2><p>XFPCB provides Prototype PCB Assembly with PCB fabrication, component sourcing, SMT, through-hole assembly and inspection coordinated in one workflow. Your BOM, CPL, Gerber files and assembly notes are reviewed together so the build plan is clear before parts and boards move to the line.</p><p>For PCBA quotations, send Gerber files, BOM with manufacturer part numbers, pick-and-place data, assembly drawing, polarity notes, DNP list and test requirements. XFPCB can then align PCB fabrication, sourcing, assembly and inspection in one plan.</p><p>For Prototype PCB Assembly, XFPCB combines engineering review, manufacturing preparation, quality inspection and export communication so your purchasing team can move from RFQ to delivery with a clear build plan.</p></div><aside class="service-panel accent"><h3>RFQ Priorities</h3><ul class="service-list"><li>BOM readiness</li><li>small batch SMT</li><li>functional test notes</li><li>engineering change feedback</li></ul></aside></div></section>
        <section class="service-section dark"><div class="service-wrap"><h2>Order Workflow</h2><div class="service-process-grid"><article class="service-step"><h3>File Review</h3><p>Review PCB files, BOM, CPL and assembly drawing together.</p></article><article class="service-step"><h3>Parts Check</h3><p>Check component availability, polarity, package and substitutes.</p></article><article class="service-step"><h3>Assembly Setup</h3><p>Prepare stencil, SMT/THT sequence and inspection plan.</p></article><article class="service-step"><h3>Inspection and Shipment</h3><p>Assemble, inspect and support shipment or functional test requirements.</p></article></div></div></section>
        <section class="service-section"><div class="service-wrap service-two-col"><div><h2>How XFPCB Controls the Build</h2><ul class="service-list"><li>BOM, CPL, Gerber files and assembly drawings are reviewed together before the build.</li><li>Component package, polarity, rotation and DNP information are checked before placement.</li><li>Stencil, SMT, THT and mixed-technology sequence are prepared according to the board design.</li><li>AOI, visual inspection, X-ray or functional test support can be added when required.</li></ul></div><figure class="service-inline-image"><img src="/images/pcba-quality-inspection-testing.png" alt="Prototype PCB Assembly workflow at XFPCB" loading="lazy"><figcaption>Prototype PCB Assembly production support at XFPCB includes file review, manufacturing preparation, inspection and shipment communication for global electronics customers.</figcaption></figure></div></section>
        <section class="service-section dark"><div class="service-wrap"><h2>Quotation Details</h2><div class="service-table-wrap"><table class="service-table"><thead><tr><th>Project Area</th><th>XFPCB Guidance</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Best use</td><td>EVT, DVT, pilot run and engineering validation</td></tr><tr><td>Needed files</td><td>Gerber, BOM, pick-and-place and assembly drawing</td></tr><tr><td>Customer benefit</td><td>One feedback loop for PCB and assembly issues</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class="service-card-grid"><article class="service-card"><h3>BOM readiness</h3><p>XFPCB reviews BOM readiness against your submitted files, quantity and application requirements before confirming the build plan.</p></article><article class="service-card"><h3>small batch SMT</h3><p>Clear small batch SMT requirements help our team quote accurately, prepare production data and reduce avoidable clarification rounds.</p></article><article class="service-card"><h3>functional test notes</h3><p>Our engineers confirm details for functional test notes early, so your team can approve the order with clear next steps.</p></article></div></div></section>
        <section class="service-section"><div class="service-wrap service-two-col"><article class="service-panel"><h2>Useful Terms</h2><dl class="service-dl"><dt>BOM</dt><dd>Bill of materials listing every component.</dd><dt>CPL</dt><dd>Component placement list showing coordinates and rotation.</dd><dt>AOI</dt><dd>Automated optical inspection after assembly.</dd><dt>Reflow</dt><dd>Heating process that solders SMT components.</dd></dl></article><article class="service-panel"><h2>Related XFPCB Pages</h2><ul class="service-list"><li><a href="/pcba-manufacturing/">PCBA Manufacturing</a></li><li><a href="/pcb-assembly/smt-pcb-assembly/">SMT PCB Assembly</a></li><li><a href="/pcb-assembly/full-turnkey-pcb-assembly-service/">Turnkey PCB Assembly</a></li><li><a href="/pcb-assembly/components-purchasing-services/">Component Sourcing</a></li></ul></article></div></section><section class="service-section dark"><div class="service-wrap"><h2>Prototype PCB Assembly FAQs</h2><div class="service-faq-grid"><details class="service-faq"><summary>What should I send to quote Prototype PCB Assembly?</summary><p>Send Gerber files, NC drill files, board outline, stackup notes, material, copper weight, surface finish, quantity and target lead time. For PCBA or assembly-related work, also send the BOM with manufacturer part numbers, pick-and-place data, assembly drawing, DNP notes and test expectations.</p></details><details class="service-faq"><summary>Can XFPCB review the files before production?</summary><p>Yes. XFPCB can review manufacturability and quotation details before production starts. We check material choices, via structures, component package data, tolerance requirements and inspection requirements before release.</p></details><details class="service-faq"><summary>Can XFPCB support both prototype and production orders?</summary><p>In most cases XFPCB can support both stages. Prototype builds help validate the design, while production planning controls repeatability, documentation, component supply and cost for future orders.</p></details><details class="service-faq"><summary>How can I reduce quotation delays?</summary><p>Provide complete files, expected annual or batch quantity, destination country, special standards, inspection needs and the target schedule. If the design is still changing, tell us which details are fixed and which are under review.</p></details></div></div></section><section class="service-section" id="quote"><div class="service-wrap service-quote-grid"><div><h2>Request a Quote for Prototype PCB Assembly</h2><p>Send your project information to XFPCB and our team will review the key manufacturing or assembly details. A complete RFQ helps us respond with a more accurate quote and a clearer production plan.</p><ul class="service-list"><li>For bare PCB projects, include Gerber, drill, stackup, material, copper, finish, quantity and lead time.</li><li>For PCBA projects, include BOM, pick-and-place file, assembly drawing, test notes and approved alternatives.</li><li>For application-specific projects, share operating environment, reliability expectations and packaging needs.</li></ul></div><form class="service-form" action="https://api.web3forms.com/submit" method="POST"><input type="hidden" name="access_key" value="40f0bc17-2a5a-45e0-85cf-99aa9d8b06df"><input type="hidden" name="honeypot" style="display:none;"><input type="hidden" name="page_url" value="https://xfpcb.com/pcb-assembly/fast-prototype-pcb-assembly-service/"><input type="hidden" name="page_path" value="/pcb-assembly/fast-prototype-pcb-assembly-service/"><input type="hidden" name="page_title" value="Prototype PCB Assembly"><input type="hidden" name="site_host" value="xfpcb.com"><input type="hidden" name="subject" value="Prototype PCB Assembly Inquiry from XFPCB Website"><input type="hidden" name="redirect" value="https://xfpcb.com/"><label for="name">Name / Company *</label><input id="name" type="text" name="name" autocomplete="name" required><label for="email">Work Email *</label><input id="email" type="email" name="email" autocomplete="email" required><label for="message">Project Details *</label><textarea id="message" name="message" rows="6" placeholder="Quantity, layer count, material, board size, BOM status, assembly or testing requirements, target lead time..." required></textarea><button type="submit">Send Inquiry</button></form></div></section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
